He said his cousin also was injured in the collapse , but that other members of his family were spared because they were out working in the fields of hard - hit Longmen village in Lushan County . Two soldiers assisting in the rescue efforts died after their vehicle slid off a road and rolled down a cliff , state media reported . The Chinese Red Cross said it had deployed relief teams with supplies of food , water , medicine and rescue equipment to the disaster areas . However , many residents complained that although emergency teams were quick to carry away bodies and search for survivors , they had so far done little to distribute aid .